defaultWhy do we pay some subsidies when there is no market for what we 
defaultsubsidi
defaultse
default?. If people don’t want to buy wool or beef then the market should decide. How long do we support a non sustainable industry? Do we continue to pay unemployed bobbin makers or crinoline designers? There are alternative uses for land.
default&#xa0;
defaultIf sheep don’t pay then perhaps timber will. Break the vicious circle and pay to diversify not continue a dead industry. If an industry is failing then public funds are used to retrain the staff not pay them indefinitely.
